{"id":55216,"date":"2024-03-27T11:09:00","date_gmt":"2024-03-27T05:39:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=55216"},"modified":"2024-03-28T13:27:12","modified_gmt":"2024-03-28T07:57:12","slug":"platform-bed-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/platform-bed-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"What&#8217;s The Hype Around Platform Bed: Why? What? &amp; How"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>The Ultimate Guide to Platform Beds: Design, Storage, and Ideas<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A good bed leads to a good night&#8217;s sleep- we all know that!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Out of all the furniture in our bedroom, the bed takes centre stage with its massive size and cosy offerings. Looking at the market prices, design options, and homeowner preferences, if a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/bedroom-design\/\">bedroom interior<\/a> trend has been dominating the market, it is<em> platform beds.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is a Platform Bed?&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A platform bed is a low-raised bed frame with wooden slats or a flat platform (like a base) to support your mattress. Unlike traditional beds, it doesn&#8217;t require a box spring or added foundation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To compare the two, platform beds are space-saving, budget-friendly, and super stylish &#8211; thanks to their <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/modern-bed-designs\/\">modern bed designs<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/28131502\/brown-and-pink-platform-bed-design.jpg\" alt=\"Brown and pink platform bed design with a low-raised bed frame\" class=\"wp-image-55225\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/28131502\/brown-and-pink-platform-bed-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.